<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870721-0129 </DOCNO><HL> Moog to Sell Carleton Unit</HL><DD> 07/21/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MOGATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> EAST AURORA, N.Y.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Moog Inc. said it signed a definitive agreement to sell its Carleton Group unit to FR Group PLC for $25 million.    As previously reported, FR Group had agreed to buy the unit, which makes pneumatic equipment, in May for $30 million. Under terms of the new agreement, Moog said FR Group agreed to assume some additional liabilities.    Moog, a maker of motion control systems and components, said it hopes to close the transaction by mid-August. FR Group, based in Dorset, England, is a holding company with interests in manufacturing aviation equipment. </TEXT></DOC>